---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Support — Reliquery" description="Get help with Reliquery: contact, FAQ, and troubleshooting for the Audit, Scout, and Forge modes.">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 prose-styles">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-ink">Support</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink/50 mt-2">We're a small team. We read every email.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-primary/20 bg-primary/5 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider">Contact</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
        Email <a href="mailto:support@reliquery.app" class="text-primary font-semibold underline">support@reliquery.app</a>
        for bug reports, feature requests, billing questions, or anything else.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink/60">
        Typical response time: 1–2 business days. For faster triage, include your Chrome version,
        the page URL you were analyzing, and a screenshot of the issue.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-12">Getting started</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
      Reliquery lives in the Chrome side panel. Pin the extension and click its icon to open the panel,
      then choose a mode based on what you're doing:
    </p>

    <div class="mt-5 grid gap-3">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-primary uppercase tracking-wider">Audit · Protect</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-ink/80 text-sm">
          On a page on <em>your own</em> site, click <b>Analyze This Page</b>. Reliquery scores brand
          alignment against your Brand Reliquary documents and lists drift findings with citations.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">Scout · Learn</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-ink/80 text-sm">
          On a competitor page, click <b>Analyze This Page</b>. Reliquery returns a side-by-side
          competitive report with strengths, weaknesses, and an exportable battle card.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-black/10 bg-white p-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-accent bg-clip-text text-transparent">Forge · Build</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-ink/80 text-sm">
          Type a design instruction in plain English ("make the hero CTA more prominent"). Reliquery
          captures a screenshot, asks Claude Opus what to change, and applies the CSS/HTML live to the page.
          Forge requires your own Anthropic API key.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-12">Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-8">Why does Chrome show a "debugging this browser" banner during Forge?</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
      Forge uses the Chrome DevTools Protocol to capture full-page screenshots and apply CSS/HTML
      changes live to the page. Whenever Forge is active, Chrome displays its standard debugging
      banner with a <b>Cancel</b> button so you always know the extension has access.
      Reliquery never uses the debugger API for monitoring, network interception, or any background activity.
      The session is detached as soon as you navigate the tab or reset the Forge session.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-8">How do I set up Forge with my own API key?</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
      Open the side panel, switch to Forge, and paste your Anthropic API key into the setup field.
      The key is stored in <code>chrome.storage.local</code> on your machine and is never transmitted
      to Reliquery. You can get a key at <a href="https://console.anthropic.com" class="text-primary underline">console.anthropic.com</a>.
      All Forge usage is billed to and visible in your own Anthropic account.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-8">How do I connect a Brand Reliquary?</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
      In the side panel settings, choose either a <b>GitHub repository</b> (paste the repo URL plus an
      optional branch and path; private repos require a personal access token with read-only repo scope)
      or a <b>local folder</b> via Chrome's File System Access API. Brand documents are read at
      analysis time, sent with the request, and never persisted server-side.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-8">Why does Audit refuse to run on sites other than my own?</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
      Audit is gated to your <b>Home Base</b> domain — the URL you set as your own site. This prevents
      accidentally auditing a competitor's page against your brand standards. To change your Home Base,
      open the side panel settings.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-8">Why does Scout refuse to run on my website?</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
      Scout is gated <em>away</em> from your Home Base domain — you can't scout your own site against
      itself. Use Audit for your own pages and Scout for competitors.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-8">Where is my data stored?</h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ink/80">
      All settings (Brand Reliquary URL, Home Base, API keys) are stored locally in your browser via
      Chrome's storage API. Page content and brand documents are sent to Reliquery's backend per request
      and discarded after the response. See the
      <a href="/privacy" class="text-primary underline">privacy policy</a> for the full breakdown.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-12">Reporting a bug</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
      Email <a href="mailto:support@reliquery.app" class="text-primary underline">support@reliquery.app</a>
      with as much of the following as you can:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 text-ink/80 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li>Reliquery extension version (visible in <code>chrome://extensions</code> → Reliquery)</li>
      <li>Chrome version and operating system</li>
      <li>The mode you were using (Audit, Scout, or Forge)</li>
      <li>The URL of the page you were analyzing (if not confidential)</li>
      <li>A screenshot of the side panel showing the error</li>
      <li>The exact error message, if any</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-12">Account and billing</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink/80">
      For account changes, refunds, plan changes, or billing questions, email
      <a href="mailto:support@reliquery.app" class="text-primary underline">support@reliquery.app</a>.
      We do not currently offer a self-service billing portal — every account change is handled by hand
      so we can confirm it's the right call for you.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink mt-12">Other</h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 text-ink/80 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
      <li><a href="/privacy" class="text-primary underline">Privacy policy</a></li>
      <li><a href="/terms" class="text-primary underline">Terms of service</a></li>
      <li>Operated by Paladinmusic Enterprises, LLC</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Base>
